SIMPLE: flasher
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flasher
<hw>Flash"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, flashes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A man of more appearance of wit than
reality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A large sparoid fish
of the Atlantic coast and all tropical seas (<spn>Lobotes
Surinamensis</spn>).</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The European red-backed
shrike (<spn>Lanius collurio</spn>); -- called also
<altname>flusher</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An exhibitionist{1}, especially a male, who briefly
exposes his private parts in a public place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>flash-frozen</ent>⟦br⟧
